So after fiddling around with the Smallrye code we came up with this solution:

```java
var propertiesFileResource = PropertiesConfigSourceProvider.propertiesSources(&quot;tenant.properties&quot;,
        this.getClass().getClassLoader());

var smallryeConfig = new SmallRyeConfigBuilder()
        .withSources(propertiesFileResource)
        .withMapping(BananaConfig.class)
        .build();

return smallryeConfig.getConfigMapping(BananaConfig.class, &quot;banana&quot;);
```
which does the job.

Note:
- this code doesn&#39;t fail with `FileNotFoundException` when the `tenant.properties` is not readable, but rather a `ConfigValidationException` because a required property was not found in any of the configuration sources. This is due to the fact that Jakarta Config uses multiple configuration sources for resolving configuration properties. You need to check the readability of the properties file yourself.

